abstract: Asda Group, the U.K. supermarket chain owned by Wal-Mart, said Thursday that it had agreed to buy the British operations of Netto Foodstores from Dansk Supermarked for $1.13 billion.
snippet: Asda Group, the U.K. supermarket chain owned by Wal-Mart, said Thursday that it had agreed to buy the British operations of Netto Foodstores from Dansk Supermarked for $1.13 billion.
lead_paragraph: Asda Group, the British supermarket chain owned by Wal-Mart, has gone and done a little shopping of its own.

headline.main: Asda Buys Netto in $1.1 Billion Deal
